{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17514367","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17514367"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T13:21:20+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T13:21:20+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12310"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"12310","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12310"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.15,0.56,0.13,0.08,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4831"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78068"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4831","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4831"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12310"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63490"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"164"},{"type":"tags","id":"1091"},{"type":"tags","id":"1193"},{"type":"tags","id":"1282"},{"type":"tags","id":"3583"},{"type":"tags","id":"3856"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4975"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"7777"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7790"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26738"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42734"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78068","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78068"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 40-year-old man presents with a 3-day history of headache around left eye with watering of the same eye and a runny nose. He has had about two episodes a day, each lasting for around 30 minutes. He had a similar episode six months ago which resolved after one day. He does not have any other current health issues apart from long-sightedness. He did have a peptic ulcer three years ago which resolved with triple therapy. He has a 15 pack-year smoking history and drinks two glass of wine a day. On examination his blood pressure is 130/85 mmHg, pulse 88/min and temperature 37.2\u003Csup\u003Eo\u003C/sup\u003EC. His left red eye is reddened and there is a partial left ptosis with a pinpoint pupil. The rest of the examination is unremarkable.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Intravenous acetazolamide","Pure oxygen inhalation","Topical pilocarpine","Ibuprofen","Carbamazepine"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe case scenario describes a cluster headache.\u003Cem\u003E \u003C/em\u003EThe first step in management is \u003Cstrong\u003Epure oxygen inhalation, \u003C/strong\u003Eat the rate of 7 L/min. In most cases the symptoms subside in 15-20 minutes. The oxygen therapy has proven positive effects, and hence is one of the most popular methods used for the treatment of acute attack of cluster headache. The other option commonly used is subcutaneous injection of sumatriptan which is a more realistic treatment option, but it is not provided as an option in this case. The mainstay of treatment is preventative.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECluster headache causes severe, unilateral peri-orbital pain with autonomic features such as unilateral lacrimation, nasal congestion and conjunctival injection, ipsilateral miosis or ptosis. The pain, though severe, is characteristically brief (30\u201390 minutes).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntravenous acetazolamide \u003C/strong\u003Eis the first line of treatment of acute closed angle glaucoma when the intraocular pressure (IOP) exceeds 50 mmHg\u003Cstrong\u003E \u003C/strong\u003Eand has no role in the treatment of cluster headache\u003Cstrong\u003E. \u003C/strong\u003EAcetazolamide is a reversible inhibitor of the carbonic anhydrase enzyme, it inactivates carbonic anhydrase and interferes with the sodium pump, which decreases aqueous humor formation and thus lowers the IOP. Acute closed angle glaucoma causes severe pain, redness and watering in the effected eye, halos around light, reduced vision, nausea and vomiting and a dilated pupil.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETopical pilocarpine \u003C/strong\u003Eis also an effective treatment option for acute closed angle glaucoma when IOP is below 50 mm of Hg. Pilocarpine is a cholinergic agonist which constricts the pupil, pulling the peripheral iris away from the trabecula, opening the anterior angle, so it has no role in the management of cluster headache.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECarbamazepine \u003C/strong\u003Eis the treatment of choice for trigeminal neuralgia and therefore is not a good option here in this case of cluster headache. Trigeminal neuralgia is characterised by unilateral lancinating facial pain, most commonly involving the second or third divisions of the trigeminal nerve territory. It tends to occur in older patients (\u0026gt;50 years). It is triggered by chewing, brushing teeth, talking, breeze lightly blowing over face or by simply touching affected areas on the face.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIbuprofen \u003C/strong\u003Eis non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug and these are used for pain relief, control of inflammation and fever. Although this class of drug has significant analgesic properties, they have not been found to be very effective in cluster headache. This patient also has a history of peptic ulcer disease which is a contraindication for an NSAID.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The first step in the management of cluster headache is pure oxygen inhalation.","Cluster headaches are characterised by severe unilateral peri-orbital pain with autonomic features such as lacrimation and nasal congestion."],"references":["Beck E, Sieber WJ, Trejo R. Management of cluster headache. Am Fam Physician. 2005 Feb 15. 71(4):717-24 Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22650381/","Beck E, Sieber WJ, Trejo R. Management of cluster headache. Am Fam Physician. 2005 Feb 15. 71(4):717-24. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/15742909/","Kandel SA, Mandiga P. Cluster Headache. [Updated 2023 Jul 4]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2025 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK544241/","Malu OO, Bailey J, Hawks MK. Cluster Headache: Rapid Evidence Review. Am Fam Physician. 2022 Jan 1;105(1):24-32. PMID: 35029932. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35029932/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63490"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12310"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63490","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63490"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-09T12:44:32+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-09T12:45:18+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4831"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78068"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"se